				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$>40^{\circ}$\end{document} from both the IBEX Ribbon center and the symmetry plane containing the LISMF and LISM flow. The temporal evolution of the LISMF observed on V1 appeared to approach the direction of the Ribbon center during quiet periods unperturbed by shocks, but evolves away from the Ribbon center during active periods (Schwadron and McComas 2017). This indicates that V1 remains in the draped LISMF in a dynamic region of space (Burlaga and Ness 2016).

